  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-crab-and-clotted-cream-risotto/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 3 min or until softened but not coloured</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-crab-and-clotted-cream-risotto/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and add your <strong>saffron</strong>, then leave to infuse – this is your <strong>saffron stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-crab-and-clotted-cream-risotto/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>with your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the<strong> saffron stock </strong>a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-crab-and-clotted-cream-risotto/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the juice of<strong> half </strong>your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>to a mixing bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and whisk to combine – this is your <strong>lemon dressing</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-crab-and-clotted-cream-risotto/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the risotto is ready, remove it from the heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: Your risotto should be porridge-like in consistency so if it is looking a little dry, add a splash of water</p><p>Stir most of your <strong>crab meat</strong> (save some for garnish!) and your <strong>clotted cream</strong> through the risotto – this is your <strong>saffron, crab & clotted cream risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-crab-and-clotted-cream-risotto/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Toss the <strong>salad</strong> in the<strong> lemon dressing</strong> – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/saffron-crab-and-clotted-cream-risotto/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>saffron, crab & clotted cream risotto</strong> topped with the <strong>dressed salad </strong>and <strong>reserved crab meat</strong> with a <strong>lemon wedge </strong>to the side</p><p>Season generously with <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
